Hi,for the benefit of everyone here 9 = 162 and 17 = 306.   Multiply or divide by 18 to convert units.Considering that normal blood sugars should be in the range of 3.8 - 7.7 (70 - 140, and ideally in the middle of this range), your sugars are high.If these levels are unusually high for you, then I would suggest you see a dr to find a cause.  Common causes can be infection of some sort.If these levels are not unusual for you, then I would suggest you work with your diabetes educator to appropriate increase your insulin dose and / or reduce the amount of carbs you eat.Hope this helps.
